      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROGUE BANDIT (4) was down the track in the Nutrien Final at Listed level last start but did manage a fresh placing in a heat of that series. He'll enjoy a class drop and draws well so may be hard to stop. CAPTAIN VALIENTE (9) is a gelding by Captain Crunch on debut for Aaron Williams. Has shown ability in winning his last two trials here, the latest by a handy margin. Drawn to enjoy an economical run so can kick off with a good showing. SEVENTH AVENUE (11) has come from this row in his two starts at this circuit and distance to date, winning on debut before a solid fourth after racing parked last week. May need a touch of luck but has upside. ELECTRICUTE (6) disappointed last time but did have a back row draw. Had been tacking good company prior so is worth another chance.",
